From: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 20:11:56 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/ops-common: use nr_accesses moving sum for score

Since commit 42f994b71404 ("mm/damon/core: implement scheme-specific
apply interval"), DAMOS scheme can be applied at any time.  At that
time, nr_accesses may not fully aggregated.  But the quota
prioritization score is calculated using the not fully aggregated count.
Fix by using damon_nr_accesses_mvsum() instead.

Fixes: 42f994b71404 ("mm/damon/core: implement scheme-specific apply interval")
Cc: <stable@vger.kernel.org> # 6.7.x
Signed-off-by: SJ Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/ops-common.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mm/damon/ops-common.c b/mm/damon/ops-common.c
index de9a104e88321..c24ce95f9f2be 100644
--- a/mm/damon/ops-common.c
+++ b/mm/damon/ops-common.c
@@ -111,7 +111,7 @@ int damon_hot_score(struct damon_ctx *c, struct damon_region *r,
 	unsigned int age_weight = s->quota.weight_age;
 	int hotness;
 
-	freq_subscore = r->nr_accesses * DAMON_MAX_SUBSCORE /
+	freq_subscore = damon_nr_accesses_mvsum(r, c) * DAMON_MAX_SUBSCORE /
 		damon_nr_samples_per_aggr(&c->attrs);
 
 	age_in_sec = (unsigned long)r->age * c->attrs.aggr_interval / 1000000;
-- 
2.47.3

